						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/Commodities/Fisheries/Related-developments/Uganda-how-to-go-into-fish-farming" title="Uganda: how to go into fish farming" alt="link">Uganda: how to go into fish farming</a></h2>

	
					<p>The market for fish is widespread and readily available due to the falling catches in water bodies countrywide. As a result, the cost of fish has tripled in five years. A kilogramme of tilapia costs sh5,000 whereas that of nile perch costs sh7,500. Due to the overwhelming scarcity, many Ugandans depend on fish bones from processing factories. (Source: The New Vision, Kikonyogo Ngatya, 28 January 2009)</p>
							<p><span class="date">10/02/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
